examples.en: She's always crawling to the boss.
There's a bug crawling up your leg.
The whole place was crawling with cops.
After the explosion, the town was crawling with soldiers.
There's a little beast crawling up your back!
The cheap room was dark, dirty, and crawling with spiders.
She lifted up the rock and found ants crawling underneath.
The crocodile was crawling along the riverbed.
Most babies begin to locomote  by crawling  when they are seven to ten months old.
I had the feeling of something crawling across my foot.
The old cheese was crawling with maggots.
The room was crawling with roaches and other vermin.
The soldiers were furtively crawling through the night.
